[NPC] Ferryd: It is for this reason that he now needs our help.
[NPC] Ferryd: Now, normally I would love a jaunt off to him, but I have some business with Menita.
[NPC] Ferryd: Lucky for me you are here, aye?
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd winks.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Go on out there tell him I sent you and see what he wants.

[To] Trasok Starhammer

[NPC Internal] Ferryd Shillor sent me.
[NPC] Trasok: You?
[NPC] Trasok: Haven't I seen you in and out of here before?
[NPC Narrate] -Trasok puts his hammer down and flicks his hand.-
[NPC] Trasok: Doesn't matter if i have…
[NPC] Trasok: My dilemma is as follows, I have ta' forge a part for the winch that is so heavy that even I lack the strength to move it with ease.
[NPC] Trasok: No one strong enough can handle it with the precision that is needed.
[NPC] Trasok: I am aware there is a strength spell that I was taught while in my training with the Reds and Ferryd.
[NPC Narrate] -Trasok utters the last words with respect but hardly any admiration.-
[NPC] Trasok: You see, I seem to have misplaced the Might Glyph that is needed for the task.
[NPC] Trasok: I am a business man, so I'll make you this offer.
[NPC] Trasok: If you would give me one, I will in return give you one of the more scarce and most powerful Red Way glyphs you will ever come across.
[NPC Narrate] -Trasok holds his hand out with a Red Way glyph awaiting the exchange.-
[NPC] Trasok: My skill with Red Way is nowhere near high enough to use it myself.
[NPC Internal] One Might glyph for our exchange.
[NPC] Trasok: Wise choice indeed.
[NPC Narrate] -Trasok looks pleased with himself.-
[NPC] Trasok: I could have traded that for at least three or four glyphs.
[NPC] Trasok: So treat it with the respect it deserves.
[NPC] Trasok: Oh, and tell Fe…
[NPC] Trasok: Archmaster Ferryd I say thank you.
[NPC] Trasok: No wait.
[NPC] Trasok: Even better, hand him your new glyph and show him what a great trade you have made.
[NPC Narrate] -Trasok starts laughing.-

[To] Ferryd Shillor

[NPC Internal] I have just traded Trasok for this Chaos glyph.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd looks surprised then seems to realise something.-
[NPC] Ferryd: I see what happened here, he traded you a valuable glyph for this.
[NPC] Ferryd: What have you lost?
[NPC] Ferryd: Tell me.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd holds up his hand and laughs.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Wait I know, it is a Might Glyph.
[NPC] Ferryd: It is the same glyph I traded him for this very same one.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd starts laughing again.-
[NPC] Ferryd: I will admit I enjoy a good prank from time to time, I believe Trasok thought this was one of them.
[NPC] Ferryd: Trasok stopped advancing in Red Way very early and would not have gotten to the skill to use it.
[NPC] Ferryd: So Trasok tried to play a prank on one of my students and pranked himself yet again.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd is about to hand you back the glyph, but pauses to changes it to another.-
[NPC] Ferryd: I certainly do appreciate a good laugh so will replace your Might glyph for you.
[NPC] Ferryd: But before I do I want you to tell me about the glyph you just received?
[NPC Internal] [You hold the glyph in your hand and concentrate and answer; Chaos.]
[NPC] Ferryd: That is the most obvious answer.
[NPC] Ferryd: But also the most important, the Chaos glyph imparts the ability to both control and release 'chaos'.
[NPC] Ferryd: Understanding the full aspect of every glyph you come into contact with will greatly improve your proficiency as a mage.
[NPC Internal] [You hold the glyph in your hand and concentrate and answer; Entropy.]
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd nods.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Wrong…
[NPC] Ferryd: Well, no, right.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd winks at you.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Chaos and Entropy go hand in hand and the ability to control Red Way Chaos will let you effects its entropy as well.
[NPC Internal] [You hold the glyph in your hand and concentrate and answer; Random.]
[NPC] Ferryd: Again this is another aspect of this glyph.
[NPC] Ferryd: If you think about Chaos you may also think about things being Random.
[NPC] Ferryd: But this is also something to be wary off, as no matter how much control you think you have Chaos, or Randomness…
[NPC] Ferryd: COULD BLOW OFF AN ARM.
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd throws his arms in the air.-
[NPC] Ferryd: POW!!!!
[NPC] Ferryd: If that happens then you'd wish you paid more attention to what I'm telling you.
[NPC Internal] [You hold the glyph in your hand and concentrate and answer; Destruction.]
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd almost yells back at you.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Destruction!!
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd snickers a little bit.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Red Way is about power and strength and fury, all of these invariably lead to destruction.
[NPC Internal] [You hold the glyph in your hand and concentrate and answer; Confusion.]
[NPC] Ferryd: Yes, Chaos and Confusion.
[NPC] Ferryd: Sound similar, no?
[NPC Internal] Lastly Fire?
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd chuckles.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Fire plays a strong role in The Red Way.
[NPC] Ferryd: But is does not mean it has to be a part of each of it's glyphs.
[NPC] Ferryd: I think you deserve to have your Might glyph now
[NPC Narrate] -Ferryd hands you your glyph.-
[NPC] Ferryd: Now, for your last task as an Apprentice, I want you to return your Lower Red Way Wand to Levrus.
[NPC] Ferryd: Return to me after you have done so and I will have your first Adept item ready.

