[NPC Internal] I was told to hand you this wand.
[NPC] Levrus: A wand?
[NPC Narrate] -Levrus shakes it.-
[NPC] Levrus: Good, it doesn't rattle so you haven't broken it.
[NPC] Levrus: Now, what would I do with such a thing?
[NPC] Levrus: I am in spectacular shape and my trousers fit quite nicely.
[NPC] Levrus: Made by the finest tailors, you see.
[NPC] Levrus: But, since you are offering it too me, I can not refuse.
[NPC Narrate] -Levrus takes a familiar box from under his counter and drops your wand in, then shakes it from side to side.-
[NPC] Levrus: What is this?
[NPC] Levrus: I seem to have a few items in here already.
[NPC] Levrus: And one is another wand.
[NPC] Levrus: Imagine that.
[NPC] Levrus: I do wonder where they keep coming from.
